+
+OPTIONS:
+  --name  <string>  Source name (human-readable key) [required]
+  --path  <path>  Path to the source repo (relative to workspace file or project root)
+  --url  <string>  Git remote URL (HTTPS or SSH) for the source
+  --branch  <string>  Git branch/ref to checkout
+  --role  <string>  Source role: artifacts, codebase, kits, full (default: full)
+  --adapter  <path>  Path to cypilot dir within the source
+  --inline  <boolean>  Add source inline to config/core.toml instead of standalone workspace file
+  --force  <boolean>  Replace existing source with the same name instead of returning an error
+
+EXIT CODES:
+  0  Source added successfully
+  1  Error (no project root, no workspace config, --inline conflict with standalone, Git URL with inline)
+  2  Invalid arguments (missing required --path or --url, or both provided)
+
+OUTPUT:
+  JSON object with:
+  - status: ADDED
+  - message: Human-readable description of the action
+  - config_path: Path to workspace config file (standalone .cypilot-workspace.toml or inline core.toml)
+  - source: Object with name, role (always present); path (when path-based), url (when URL-based); adapter, branch (included only when set)
+  - replaced: true if an existing source was overwritten (omitted for new sources)
+
+EXAMPLE:
+  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --name docs --path ../docs-repo --role artifacts
+  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --name lib --url https://gitlab.com/team/lib.git --branch main
+  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py workspace-add --inline --name docs --path ../docs-repo --role artifacts
